A Team USA Triathlete
On the job, Khadijah Diggs is helping Southern Company build the future of energy. Off the clock, she is a Team USA triathlete in training for this year’s world championships. Khadijah approaches her role with Southern Company Services’ program management office with commitment and determination. She applies that same energy and discipline as she prepares to compete for her country.


































The energy to compete for our country












“I just ran. I didn’t think about anything. When I crossed the line my run coach ran to me, grabbed me and said ‘you did it!’ It was pretty emotional.”




























Merger News

                  Southern Company and AGL Resources have merged, creating America's leading U.S. electric and gas utility company.
                  





















Kemper County Energy Facility

                  Our facility in Mississippi will be a state-of-the-art power plant that converts coal to gas to produce electricity with reduced emissions.
                  





















Plant Vogtle 3 and 4

                  Plant Vogtle units 3 and 4 will be the first in the industry to use the Westinghouse AP1000 advanced pressurized water reactor technology.
                  





























