 Volvo Penta – Southern Power



























 














 




Volvo Penta 




Volvo Penta’s Inboard Performance System (IPS) with forward-facing, twin counter-rotating propellers is developed as a modern, alternative to traditional inboard shafts. Combined with its individually steerable pods under the hull, it is superior to inboard shafts in every vital aspect – handling, onboard comfort and performance. Volvo Penta IPS comes as complete packages, from one supplier, for twin, triple or quadruple diesel installations – making forward-facing efficiency available for yachts from 30 to 100 feet.
FEATURES
Petrol Propulsion Engines | Diesel Propulsion Engines, Commercial and Leisure | Marine Generators | IPS Propulsion Systems | Accessories | Sound seal | Black Jack Shaft Seals | Propellers Fixed and Folding | Shaft and Stern Tubes | Fuel Decontaminators | Controls and Cables
UNIQUE BENEFITS of VOLVO PENTA IPS
40% longer cruising range |  20% higher top speed | 30% reduced fuel consumption | 30% less CO2 emissions |  50% lower perceived noise level | Joystick docking








