The launch and successful sea trials of the Guardrunner

	            The launch and successful sea trials of the Guardrunner mark Nautic Africa and Southern Power (SP) ability to cater to the special forces market where search and rescue (SAR) and military encounters require specialised platforms. 	        

Read On











Safe at sea appoints SPP as exclusive sub saharan african supplier

	            These versatile, robust and ‘go anywhere’ craft have been specifically designed to perform search and rescue as well as combat search and rescue operations under extreme conditions and in all water environments, including shallow waters 	        

Read On











SPP to participate in global testing phase of new engines

	            SPP is one of more than 20 Cimco global partners selected to test the new engine technology in a number of different environments and applications. Even though the new engines are not yet in production 	        

